Probabilistic Methods, Neural Networks

Probabilistic Methods: The paper discusses the use of an adaptive filter architecture and ideal inverses of acquired room impulse responses to compare the effectiveness of different-sized separating filter configurations of various filter lengths. These methods involve probabilistic modeling and estimation.

Neural Networks: The paper uses a multi-channel blind least-mean-square algorithm (MBLMS) to improve upon the separation of signals mixed with real-world filters. MBLMS is a neural network-based algorithm that uses a linear filter to separate the sources.
